# Customer Churn Prediction & Segmentation

## Executive Summary

This project presents an end-to-end Machine Learning pipeline for predicting telecom customer churn and translating those predictions into business-oriented customer segments for targeted retention strategies.

Starting from exploratory data analysis and data cleaning, the project builds a Random Forest classification model, tunes it through systematic hyperparameter search, evaluates it using cross-validation and ROC-AUC, and applies K-Means clustering to turn churn predictions into actionable business insights.

The notebook demonstrates a complete, practical data science workflow — from raw data to business recommendations.

---

## Project Objectives

* Predict telecom customer churn using supervised machine learning.
* Handle class imbalance in the churn target variable.
* Optimize model performance through systematic hyperparameter search (tree count and depth).
* Evaluate model quality using Accuracy, Recall, Precision, F1-score, cross-validation, and ROC-AUC.
* Interpret model predictions through Feature Importance Analysis.
* Segment customers using K-Means clustering based on predicted churn probability and customer behavior.
* Generate business-oriented retention strategies for each customer segment.

